Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Toyji is a social, tangible and digital entertainment platform for all ages that use smart toys as game controllers on a toy pad to play brain training video games beyond the screen. Existing educational board games are easily mastered and cannot be upgraded. That is why digital brain training games are replacing them, but these are not social or tangible.Toyji provides a better solution for parents, families, friends, and schools by featuring digital mind board games in one dynamic tabletop gaming platform with a marketplace! The human brain is plastic; it can form and reorganize synopses in response to learning. Based on that principle, Toyji’s neuroplasticity-focused educational games improve cognitive, logic, social, motor and STEM skills. Our gaming hardware is a patented portable tabletop gaming board that connects with USB or Bluetooth technology to any smart device like iOS, Android tablets, mobile phones, game consoles, Android TV's and desktop/laptop computers. Our technology allows us to detect up to 16 interchangeable, 3D-printable, customizable and interactive smart toys simultaneously by supporting two-way communication on the board, sending their ID, position and orientation data in real-time to any interactive application developed with Unity3D Game Engine with our SDK. We wanted to make something more than just a tablet game or a standalone smart toy, more than just a fun pastime, so we made Toyji, combining tangible gaming, digital entertainment and fun learning in a way that brings families, friends, and children together. Toyji is a personalized gaming platform that offers families and schools educational games taking place in a fictional universe, played with customizable and interactive smart toys.

Description: Nickel is an allowance manager for kids to gain real-world experience with money.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: The Internet is changing money—how they access it, spend it and manage it. E-commerce and mobile payments have taken virtually all of the friction out of spending, making it much easier to spend money without much thinking. Their children are growing up in this brave new economy. In this complex, ever-evolving world of money one thing never changes: the importance of teaching their kids the value of a dollar. How can they, as parents, help educate their children about making smart spending and saving decisions? By rethinking allowance. It’s time for their children’s allowance to catch up with the digital economy. It’s time to talk to their kids about money, and empower them with the tools to shape a lifetime of financial well-being. It’s time for Nickel. Nickel helps you teach your kids to think about money and manage it wisely. It’s part mobile app and part MasterCard debit card. You can set a weekly or monthly allowance, and add a favorable interest rate to encourage your child to save. The allowance is auto-paid from your bank to your child’s Nickel Card, along with the compounding interest (which you also pay). Nickel helps teens and kids ages 8 and up make conscious choices around spending vs. saving—showing them how much interest they’ve earned already, and how much more they could earn if they choose to save instead of spend. Plus, Nickel lets you take the guesswork out of wondering where and how your kids are dropping their dimes by helping you track their spending and saving. But their mission goes beyond what the technology powering the Nickel debit card and app offers. Their goal is to help parents… - Encourage children and teens to make meaningful choices around money - Teach kids the power of compound interest - Help kids save and experience the time-value of money - Spark an important, ongoing dialogue between parents and their children about the value and purpose of money, helping kids develop healthy money habits that can last a lifetime Nickel is for children and their parents. They want to help the next generation learn to manage money by facing real decisions. They believe it’s good to learn from making mistakes young while the stakes are relatively low—with $30 rather than $30,000. Together, they can create a generation that is financially empowered. They created Nickel to give families the tools and resources to help them raise money-smart kids. They’re starting with allowance. The child or teen who thinks about whether to buy something today or save at a compounded-interest rate for tomorrow can develop the habits to grow into a financially savvy adult—one who spends mindfully and invests wisely, one who aligns their money to their values. They imagine a world where youth are empowered to save for college, make smart spending decisions, and maybe even manage an investment portfolio.
Industry Groups: Community and Lifestyle, Financial Services, Food and Beverage

Description: A platform for Creators by Creators.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Baltimore-Maryland Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Creators Label was founded in 2016 trying to solve a common problem - influencer merchandising. The issue that still exists to this day is poor manufacturing processes and very poor turnaround times for end customers. In our own study we purchased merchandise from popular influencers to see what the quality standards were and how long it took for us to receive the product. We found that the average turnaround was 1-2 months from most companies and the merch that did come in fast was awful quality. Most companies outsource their printing or use a process called DTG. With DTG being a newer technology the quality is certainly not ready for retail. With outsourcing quality product you have no control on your lead times. So, we took both of those problems and developed the perfect hybrid. Quality screenprinted or embroidered product, manufactured in-house. Everything send out of our warehouse is done with utmost QC and shipped fast. We are currently developing custom technology integrating artificial intelligence. We are continuing to stay in the merchandising space however are moving towards a 360 PaaS solution for Influencers and management.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Information Technology, Manufacturing, Software
